      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix: refuse local tsgo under host pressure",
        "body": "## Summary\n- refuse local native type-aware checks by default on developer/agent hosts\n- cover `tsgo`, type-aware `oxlint`, and sharded type-aware `oxlint`\n- cover direct raw `tsgo` helper scripts: extension package boundary, core boundary, and tsgo profiling\n- keep metadata commands cheap and unblocked (`--help`, `--version`, etc.)\n- keep CI/GitHub Actions unblocked so broad native checks run online instead of on constrained hosts\n- preserve explicit break-glass overrides for local runs\n- keep pressure refusal and effective heavy-check temp-dir checks from the earlier patch\n- rebase onto current `main` and preserve upstream serial shard support\n\n## Why\nA constrained Raspberry Pi/agent host repeatedly became unstable when native type-aware checks (`tsgo`/`tsgolint` via type-aware oxlint) ran locally. Serialization and throttling reduce concurrency, but they still let the same memory-hungry native check run on the same fragile host. That is the wrong failure mode.\n\nThis PR now makes the safer default explicit: local wrappers and repo helper scripts refuse native type-aware checks unless the operator opts in. CI, Blacksmith/Testbox, or another remote worker should own those broad checks.\n\n## Behavior\nLocal native type-aware checks refuse by default when local heavy-check policy is active and mode is not `full`:\n\n- `scripts/run-tsgo.mjs`\n- `scripts/run-oxlint.mjs` when it runs type-aware oxlint, including explicit file-target runs\n- `scripts/run-oxlint-shards.mjs` before artifact prep or child shard spawning\n- `scripts/check-extension-package-tsc-boundary.mjs`\n- `scripts/check-tsgo-core-boundary.mjs`\n- `scripts/profile-tsgo.mjs`\n\nBypasses / allowed cases:\n\n- GitHub Actions / CI are not blocked\n- metadata-only commands are not blocked\n- `OPENCLAW_LOCAL_CHECK_MODE=full` allows the local run\n- `OPENCLAW_HEAVY_CHECK_FORCE=1` allows the local run\n- `OPENCLAW_ALLOW_LOCAL_NATIVE_TYPECHECK=1` allows the local run\n- child processes already covered by a parent heavy-check lock can continue without self-deadlock\n\nExisting pressure checks still refuse local heavy checks when headroom is too low:\n\n- `OPENCLAW_HEAVY_CHECK_MIN_MEM_AVAILABLE_BYTES` defaults to `1.5 GiB`\n- `OPENCLAW_HEAVY_CHECK_MIN_TMP_AVAILABLE_BYTES` defaults to `1 GiB`\n- `OPENCLAW_HEAVY_CHECK_MAX_TMP_USED_PERCENT` defaults to `80`\n\n## GitHub CI note\nGitHub CI means these checks run online on GitHub/runner machines after pushing the branch, not on the local Raspberry Pi. The PR gets pass/fail status from those remote runners.\n\n## Test Plan\nFinal head: `d5ac46f0e0ac97023b949252915853f633c4429a`\n\nLocal checks intentionally stayed narrow and refusal-only. Broad lint/test/type-aware gates are left to GitHub CI.\n\nNarrow local syntax/refusal probes run after the latest patch:\n\n- `node --check scripts/check-extension-package-tsc-boundary.mjs`\n- `node --check scripts/profile-tsgo.mjs`\n- `node --check scripts/check-tsgo-core-boundary.mjs`\n- `OPENCLAW_LOCAL_CHECK_MODE=throttled node scripts/check-extension-package-tsc-boundary.mjs --mode=compile`\n- `OPENCLAW_LOCAL_CHECK_MODE=throttled node scripts/profile-tsgo.mjs core --json`\n- `OPENCLAW_LOCAL_CHECK_MODE=throttled node scripts/check-tsgo-core-boundary.mjs`\n\nPreviously passed locally before this direct-script follow-up:\n\n- syntax checks for `run-tsgo`, `run-oxlint`, `run-oxlint-shards`, and local heavy-check runtime\n- scoped formatter/lint checks on touched wrapper files\n- `OPENCLAW_LOCAL_CHECK_MODE=throttled pnpm test test/scripts/local-heavy-check-runtime.test.ts test/scripts/run-oxlint.test.ts --run`\n- result: `Test Files 2 passed`, `Tests 34 passed`\n\n## Real behavior proof\n- **Behavior or issue addressed:** Local OpenClaw script entry points that can start native `tsgo`/`tsgolint` now refuse on developer/agent hosts by default, while sharded oxlint metadata commands (`--help`, `--version`, etc.) delegate directly without parent artifact preparation, lock acquisition, shard spawning, or heavy temp-dir creation.\n- **Real environment tested:** Raspberry Pi OpenClaw checkout on branch `fix/local-tsgo-pressure-guard`, head `d5ac46f0e0ac`, with `origin/main` fetched at `1a34c4833e62` and merge-base `7a7d9dedc14f`; local env explicitly removed `CI`/`GITHUB_ACTIONS` for refusal probes.\n- **Exact steps or command run after this patch:**\n\n```bash\ngit diff --check\n\nenv -u CI -u GITHUB_ACTIONS OPENCLAW_LOCAL_CHECK_MODE= OPENCLAW_LOCAL_HEAVY_CHECK_TMPDIR=.artifacts/proof-heavy-tmp node scripts/run-oxlint-shards.mjs\n\nenv -u CI -u GITHUB_ACTIONS OPENCLAW_LOCAL_CHECK_MODE= OPENCLAW_LOCAL_HEAVY_CHECK_TMPDIR=.artifacts/proof-heavy-tmp node scripts/run-oxlint-shards.mjs --help\n\ntest ! -e .artifacts/proof-heavy-tmp\n\nenv -u CI -u GITHUB_ACTIONS OPENCLAW_LOCAL_CHECK_MODE= OPENCLAW_LOCAL_HEAVY_CHECK_TMPDIR=.artifacts/proof-heavy-tmp node scripts/run-oxlint-shards.mjs scripts/run-tsgo.mjs\n\nenv -u CI -u GITHUB_ACTIONS OPENCLAW_LOCAL_CHECK_MODE=full OPENCLAW_HEAVY_CHECK_MIN_MEM_AVAILABLE_BYTES=999999999999999 OPENCLAW_LOCAL_HEAVY_CHECK_TMPDIR=.artifacts/proof-heavy-tmp node scripts/run-tsgo.mjs --project config/tsconfig/root.json\n```\n\n- **Evidence after fix:**\n\n```text\nHEAD=d5ac46f0e0ac\ngit diff --check: exit=0\n\n[default sharded refusal]\nexit=1\nRefusing to start sharded type-aware oxlint on this local host.\nNative type-aware checks can exhaust constrained developer/agent machines; run them in GitHub CI, Blacksmith/Testbox, or another remote worker instead.\nArguments: <default project run>\nIf you really mean to run this locally, rerun with OPENCLAW_HEAVY_CHECK_FORCE=1 or OPENCLAW_ALLOW_LOCAL_NATIVE_TYPECHECK=1.\n\n[metadata delegation / no parent temp dir]\nexit=0\nUsage: [-c=<./.oxlintrc.json>] [PATH]...\nBasic Configuration\n    -c, --config=<./.oxlintrc.json>  Oxlint configuration file\n\ntest ! -e .artifacts/proof-heavy-tmp: exit=0\n\n[explicit file-target delegation]\nexit=1\nRefusing to start type-aware oxlint on this local host.\nNative type-aware checks can exhaust constrained developer/agent machines; run them in GitHub CI, Blacksmith/Testbox, or another remote worker instead.\nArguments: scripts/run-tsgo.mjs --type-aware --tsconfig config/tsconfig/oxlint.json --report-unused-disable-directives-severity error --threads=1\nIf you really mean to run this locally, rerun with OPENCLAW_HEAVY_CHECK_FORCE=1 or OPENCLAW_ALLOW_LOCAL_NATIVE_TYPECHECK=1.\n\n[tsgo pressure refusal]\nexit=1\nRefusing to start a local heavy check because this host is already under pressure:\n- MemAvailable 11 GiB is below 909 TiB\nWait for pressure to clear, free temp space, or rerun with OPENCLAW_HEAVY_CHECK_FORCE=1 if you really mean it.\n```\n\n- **Observed result after fix:** The current head `d5ac46f0e0ac` refuses the default sharded type-aware oxlint run locally before any shard work; metadata-only `--help` delegates directly and leaves `.artifacts/proof-heavy-tmp` absent; an explicit file target delegates to the narrow oxlint wrapper and refuses there instead of spawning the sharded parent path; `run-tsgo` refuses under simulated host pressure before native type-aware work starts.\n- **What was not tested:** Broad local CI was intentionally not run on the Raspberry Pi. Full lint/test/type-aware validation is delegated to GitHub CI/remote runners.\n- **What changed because of the evidence:** The proof now covers current head `d5ac46f0e0ac` and the latest sharded oxlint refusal/setup behavior that ClawSweeper flagged as stale.\n\n",
